regular expression itself is a mini programming language specialized on matching string

to use regular expression, you must install re library. 

import re

re.search(, <string_name>)			to see if a string matches a regular expression
									the argument must be a string

re.findall()						to exstract portions of a string that matches the regular expression. 
									it returns a list.

structure
re.finall('', <string_name>)

################################################################################################
		special regular expression
@([^ ]*)

@			it find an at
()			to start and to end of the string extraction
			it means that the regular expression will keep in memory to print 
[^ ]			match non-blank character
*			match many of them 

